# Disjoint Sets Problems

## How to compile and run
g++ -std=c++17 -o dsp dsp.cpp 
./dsp.exe

## Menu options

Connected Components — enter number of nodes, then edges as "u v" on the same line (e.g. 0 1). Returns how many separate groups exist.

Cycle Detection — enter number of nodes, then edges as "u v" on the same line. Returns whether the graph has a cycle and which edge caused it.

Number of Provinces — enter matrix size n, then each row as space-separated 0s and 1s (e.g. 1 1 0). Returns how many independent city groups exist.

Friend Groups — enter number of users, then friendship pairs as "u v" on the same line. Returns how many friend groups formed and who is in each one.

Exit — exits the program